[Although a single case of botulism can be confused with a variety of other neurological illnesses, clusters of symmetrical cranial nerve palsies followed by symmetrical descending flaccid paralysis are almost always botulism. Most outbreaks are related to homemade food. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3467332,67.]
